The reason I like that staff is that it gives me a completely new way to play.  It adds to my plethora of tactics.  Clerics hardly have to heal me, even when I AE 4+ mobs and the chanter can't stun.  I would like to assume that saving  yer cleric mana is a good thing but people seem to overlooko that.  Now, should I wish, I can get a robe or staff that casts DD (and yes, you can get a robe DD on a mob that isn't in VP atm).  <br>
<br>
The only thing I could think of that would have made a unique item would be an effect that lowers the mana cost for each spell or increase the effectiveness of the DD by a percentage.  Unfortunately, a lot of these ideas would seriously, if you think about it, overpower our class.  Clarity?  Why would I want that on my item when I can just get a bard and an enchanter?  <br>
<br>
Not everyone is going to be happy with something...hard to satisfy so many people with different play styles.  I settled myself into a mini-tank wizard when I started pulling PoF as a wizard over a year ago so I am in love with this item.  I also happen to think that I should be the one taking damage rather than the enchanter so it makes it even better for me, shrugs. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
